Column tools → Data category
Set to: Country / State / Region (as applicable)

Regional performance was analyzed using bar and map visuals to compare Total Sales across geographic areas. Bar charts provide precise comparison, while maps offer intuitive geographic insights, helping identify high-performing and underperforming regions.

ADD TOP 10 PRODUCTS TABLE
1️ Create the Required Measure (If Not Already)
Go to Modeling → New measure
Total Sales = SUM('Fact_Sales'[Sales])

2️ Insert the Table Visual
Report View → Table visual

3️ Add Fields to the Table
Drag these fields:
Columns
Product Name
Total Sales
Total Profit
Profit Margin
This shows both performance and quality of products.

4️ Filter to Top 10 Products (VERY IMPORTANT)
Method: Visual-Level Filter (Best)
Select the table
Go to Filters pane
Under Filters on this visual
Drag Product Name
Change filter type to Top N
Set:
Show items: Top 10
By value: Total Sales
Click Apply filter
Now the table always shows Top 10 by Sales

5️ Sort the Table
Click on Total Sales column
Sort → Descending
Top product appears first.

6️ Format the Table (Clean & Professional)
Column Formatting
Total Sales → Currency
Total Profit → Currency
Profit Margin → Percentage
Grid
Row padding → Medium
Grid lines → Off (clean look)

7️ Optional (Advanced but Impressive)
Conditional Formatting
Profit Margin → Color scale
Red = Low
Green = High
Data Bars
Total Sales → Data bars
Makes top performers visually pop.

A Top 10 Products table was created using a visual-level Top N filter based on Total Sales. The table displays sales, profit, and profit margin, enabling identification of high-performing and high-margin products.

Top 10 Products – High Profit Contributors
Findings:

Zebra zm400 label printer, Zebra GX4290 thermal printer, Xerox multifunction printer, Xiamoi, Zebra GK4290 thermal printer
printout recycle, printout paper, note card, message books, parchmaent paper.  

The Top 10 products contribute a significant portion of total sales and profit, indicating revenue concentration.
These products show strong profit margins, making them key business drivers.
Some high-selling products generate lower margins, highlighting pricing or cost challenges.

ADD SLICERS IN POWER BI (REGION • YEAR • CATEGORY)
1️ Add Region Slicer
Steps:
Go to Report View
From Visualizations pane, select Slicer
Drag Region → Field
Format (Recommended):
Slicer type → Dropdown
Title → On
Title text → Region
Single select → Off (allow multi-select)
Use when users want to filter by geography.

2️ Add Year Slicer
Best Practice: Use Year column (not full date)
Steps:
Insert another Slicer
Drag Order Date → Field
Click dropdown on the slicer → choose Year (or drag Year column if you created one)

Format:
Slicer type → Horizontal
Title → Year
This avoids confusing date ranges and improves usability.

3️ Add Category Slicer
Steps:
Insert a Slicer
Drag Category → Field

Format:
Slicer type → List or Dropdown
Title → Category
Multi-select → On
Useful to analyze category-wise performance instantly.

4️ Arrange Slicers (Layout Tip)
Best layout:
[ Region ]   [ Year ]   [ Category ]

Steps:
Select all slicers (Ctrl + Click)
Format → Align → Top
Format → Distribute horizontally
Keeps dashboard clean and professional.

5️ Ensure Slicers Affect All Visuals
Check interactions:
Select a slicer
Go to Format → Edit interactions
Ensure Filter icon is active on all visuals
Turn off filter only if needed

6️ Optional Enhancements (Recommended)
Sync slicers (if multiple pages):
View → Sync slicers
Sync Region/Year across pages
Clear selection button:
Add a button → Action → Clear filters


Interactive slicers for Region, Year, and Category were added to allow dynamic filtering of KPIs and visuals. This enables users to explore sales performance across different dimensions and supports data-driven decision-making.

Category Performance Analysis
Findings:
Technology category generates the highest sales and profit margins, making it the most valuable category.
Office Supplies show stable sales with moderate profitability.
Furniture category, while generating significant revenue, shows lower profit margins, indicating higher costs or discounting.
Insight: High sales do not always translate into high profit. Margin analysis is critical for decision-making.

A dedicated insights section was added to summarize key business findings derived from KPI cards and visuals. This helps stakeholders quickly understand trends, category performance, and revenue concentration without interpreting individual charts.

Key Business Findings (Summary)
Sales have increased consistently over the years, indicating strong business growth.
Technology products are the most profitable, while Furniture requires cost optimization.
Revenue and profit are concentrated among a small group of top-performing products.
Regional performance varies significantly, requiring customized strategies.

Recommendations to Improve Sales & Profitability
To Increase Sales:
Focus marketing and promotional efforts on high-performing regions.
Expand availability and promotion of top-selling and high-margin products.
Improve presence in underperforming regions through targeted campaigns.

To Improve Profitability:
Optimize pricing and reduce costs in low-margin categories such as Furniture.
Limit excessive discounting on products with low profit margins.
Encourage cross-selling of high-margin products.

Strategic Improvements:
Diversify product portfolio to reduce dependency on a few top products.
Use seasonal trends to plan inventory and promotions effectively.
Monitor KPIs regularly using the dashboard for proactive decision-making.

9. Conclusion
The BI dashboard successfully transforms raw sales data into actionable insights through KPI tracking, trend analysis, and product-level profitability evaluation. By focusing on high-margin categories, strengthening regional strategies, and optimizing low-performing segments, the organization can achieve sustainable sales growth and improved profitability.

